# User Stories for 5k Race Results Application

## Entrant Management
1. As a race organizer, I want to upload one or more Excel files containing entrant details (bib number, name, club, gender, age), so that all participants are registered in the system.
2. As a race organizer, I want the system to validate uploaded entrant files and display errors if any required fields are missing or duplicated, so that data integrity is maintained.

## Finish Position & Bib Upload
3. As a race official, I want to upload an Excel file with finish positions and bib numbers, so that the system can record the order in which runners finished.
4. As a race official, I want the system to flag any bib numbers in the finish file that do not match any registered entrant, so that I can manually review and correct them.

## Finish Position & Timing Upload
5. As a race official, I want to upload an Excel file with finish positions and timings, so that the system can associate each runner’s finish time with their position.
6. As a race official, I want the system to validate that finish positions in the timing file match those in the bib file, so that results are consistent.

## Results Collation & Output
7. As a race organizer, I want the system to collate results by finish position, showing time, name, club, and gender for each runner, so that I can review and publish the final standings.
8. As a race organizer, I want the system to clearly indicate any runners who did not finish (DNF), so that the results are accurate and complete.
9. As a race organizer, I want to export the final results to a PDF file, so that I can upload it online for participants and the public to view.
